{"ts":"2026-06-24T22:17:15.689Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-zqes"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"describeExtensionBlueprint omits importer/exporter-with-options command definitions (parity gap vs describeExtensionActivation)"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"describeExtensionBlueprint (src/sdk/compose.ts) places importer/exporter synthesized command paths only in command_handlers, never in `commands`, and does not surface their option-registered flag targets or the resulting `commands` capability. But at runtime, registerImporter/registerExporter WITH options (action/description/flags) push a full RegisteredExtensionCommandDefinition (loader applyImportExportCommandMetadata), so describeExtensionActivation lists those paths under `commands`, includes their `<name> import|export` flag targets in flag_commands, and reports `commands` in capabilities. For an importer/exporter-with-options-only blueprint the two summaries diverge (commands, flag_commands, capabilities), violating the parity contract pinned in the describeExtensionBlueprint docstring. The existing parity test (buildParityBlueprint) masks this because its importers/exporters declare no options. Empirically confirmed while building pm-lfdv: an importers-only blueprint with options.flags yields static commands=[] / capabilities=[importers,schema] vs runtime commands=[tickets export,tickets import] / capabilities=[commands,importers,schema]. Fix: make describeExtensionBlueprint mirror applyImportExportCommandMetadata for entries with options (commands + flag_commands + command capability), then extend the parity test with a flag-bearing importer/exporter. Related: pm-v3ty (deriveExtensionCapabilities schema under-grant, fixed alongside pm-lfdv)."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["area:extensions","area:sdk"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-24T22:17:15.689Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-24T22:17:15.689Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"d31cbad83010b12007f9e789a907d7bd0009e772c39bc3aaa9bd9d8580619a7d","message":""}
